      <Value><![CDATA[<p><strong>When:   Thursday 8th October from 11.30am </strong></p>
<p><strong>Where:  QMU, at the bottom of stairs entering into 1875</strong></p>
<p>Meet the Sports Innovation Challenge team and find out more about how you could demonstrate your entrepreneurialism and put your innovative ideas to the test.</p>
<p><strong>The Sports Innovation Challenge</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><em>The Sports Innovation Challenge is an entrepreneurship competition for students and recent graduates to develop an innovative idea into a sports business. </em></li>
<li><em>The Challenge has a series of workshops that lead entrants through a variety of business skills such as Business Action Planning, Marketing and How to Make the Perfect Pitch (by ESpark). </em></li>
<li><em>There is a £12,000 prize fund, one year incubation and on-going industry expert mentoring support. </em></li>
<li><em>We cover students travel expenses to events. </em></li>
<li><em>Students who participate in workshops get a <strong>Practical Skills Certificate</strong> which could help <strong>CV’s, employability and life skills</strong>. </em></li>
<li><em>Whether you’re passionate about sport and/or business, the Challenge is the competition you’ve been waiting for! </em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>LoveYourIdea</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><em>LoveYourIdea is a competition for students and recent graduates about innovative ideas. </em></li>
<li><em>Students can submit an idea for a new sports product, service and/or technology and in return <strong>can win one of five cash prizes (£100-500). </strong></em></li>
<li><em>The whole submission process takes no longer than 90 seconds and is a great way to make some money from your idea. </em></li>
<li><em>One idea is all it takes, yours could earn you £500! </em></li>
</ul>]]></Value>
